# Changelog and Versioning

## Every Task (required)

Add bullet(s) under `[Unreleased]` in **AGENTS.md** section **11. Changelog and Version History** as you implement:

- `Added` — new features
- `Changed` — behavior or UX changes
- `Fixed` — bug fixes
- `Removed` — deleted features

Use English. Be specific (file/behavior), not vague.

**Changelog ≠ handover:** §11 records *what changed*; procedures for the next agent (GitHub, release, scripts, URLs) belong in **AGENTS.md §3 / §8 / §9** in the **same task**. See `.cursor/rules/immediate-handover.mdc`.

## User-facing Korean update log (required at version bump)

On **every version bump**, update **`UpdateLog/update_log.md`** (Korean) per **AGENTS.md §3.7**:

- **Grouped by patch decade** within the same `major.minor`: e.g. `v0.8.60–0.8.69`, `v0.8.70–0.8.79` (patch tens digit ×10 … ×10+9).
- **Same block:** append bullets under **추가** / **변경** / **수정** / **제거** — no per-patch `## v0.8.65` header.
- **New decade:** new `## vX.Y.A–X.Y.B (date)` section at the **top** below intro.
- No file/class names unless shown in UI; dev-only: `_(사용자 인터페이스 변경 없음)_`.
- Bulk regroup after backfill: `python scripts/regroup-update-log.py` — review Korean before release.

`AGENTS.md` §11 remains **one English section per patch version**.

## Version Bump (mandatory — every completed user task)

**Before closing the task**, bump version. Do **not** leave work only under `[Unreleased]` with an unchanged `CMakeLists.txt` version.

| Step | Action |
|------|--------|
| 1 | Increment `project(PIPBONG VERSION ...)` in `CMakeLists.txt` |
| 2 | Move all `[Unreleased]` bullets into `## [x.y.z] - YYYY-MM-DD` in **AGENTS.md** §11 |
| 3 | Append or add grouped Korean block in **`UpdateLog/update_log.md`** ([§3.7](../../AGENTS.md#37-user-facing-korean-update-log)) |
| 4 | Leave empty `[Unreleased]` section; update **Current version** at top of **AGENTS.md** |
| 5 | **Incremental build at task close** when C++/headers/`CMakeLists.txt` changed → **`.\scripts\build-release.ps1` only** (never `cmake --preset` if `build/CMakeCache.txt` exists). Skip when docs/rules-only. |
| 6 | **Backup:** `git add` / `git commit` / `git push origin main` on **`Baegovda/PIPBONG`** |
| 7 | **Release:** `.\scripts\create-github-release.ps1` (package + publish `vX.Y.Z` ZIP) — **mandatory on every version bump** |

**Do not** bump version without push + GitHub Release in the same task.

### Which segment to increment

| Type | Example |
|------|---------|
| **Patch** `0.3.0 → 0.3.1` | **Default — every completed user task** |
| **Minor** `0.3.x → 0.4.0` | New block type, major subsystem, user-facing milestone |
| **Major** `1.0.0` | Breaking project JSON format |

When in doubt, **patch bump**.

`Application.cpp` reads version from generated `PipbongVersion.h` (from `CMakeLists.txt` `PROJECT_VERSION`); do not hardcode version strings elsewhere.

Full policy: [AGENTS.md](../../AGENTS.md) — **§10 Versioning Policy**, **§11 Changelog**, **§3.7 Korean update log**, **§3.6 GitHub backup and release**, **§3.1 IDE workflow**.
